theorem Topology.interior_closure_eq_univ_iff_closure_eq_univ {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure A) = (Set.univ : Set X) ↔ closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro hInt
    -- Since `interior (closure A) = univ`, it is in particular contained in `closure A`.
    have h_subset : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
      have : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
      simpa [hInt] using this
    exact Set.Subset.antisymm (Set.Subset_univ _) h_subset
  · intro hCl
    -- Rewrite `interior (closure A)` using `closure A = univ`.
    simpa [hCl, interior_univ]

theorem Set.Subset_univ {α : Type*} {s : Set α} : s ⊆ (Set.univ : Set α) := by
  intro x _
  simp
